# Atomic Design

## Layer placement

| Layer | Folder | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| Atoms | `components/atoms/` | Button, Input, Label, Icon |
| Molecules | `components/molecules/` | FormField, TabItem, SearchBar |
| Organisms | `components/organisms/` | Header, Sidebar, TabNavigation |
| Templates | `components/templates/` | DashboardLayout, AuthLayout |
| Pages | `app/` | Route files with data + content |

## File structure

One component per file, colocated in a named folder:

```
components/atoms/button/Button.tsx
```

Import directly from the component file:

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/atoms/button/Button";
```

Do not add barrel `index.ts` re-export files.

## Rules

- Atoms: no business logic, no data fetching
- Molecules: compose atoms; single focused responsibility
- Organisms: compose molecules/atoms; reusable across pages
- Templates: layout shells with `children` slots; no route data fetching

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — page layout in atoms
components/atoms/Dashboard.tsx

// ✅ GOOD
components/templates/dashboard-layout/DashboardLayout.tsx
```
